Brazil Stock Movers: JBS, Kroton Educacional, Rossi Residencial

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-05-18T20:28:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/brazilian-stock-movers-jbs-mmx-mineracao-petroleo-brasileiro.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index dropped 1.3 percent to 62,840.61.  JBS SA (JBSS3)  (JBSS3 BS) slumped 5 percent to 5.48 reais. The
world’s biggest beef producer said its board agreed to increase
capital by as much as 3.48 billion reais ($2.15 billion) through
a private placement.  Kroton Educacional SA (KROT11 BS) dropped the most since
June 2009, losing 5.3 percent to 20.45 reais. The Brazilian
administrator of private schools and colleges plans to sell
stock equivalent to as much as 39 percent of its total market
value. The company plans to raise as much as 570.71 million
reais, based on the stock’s May 13 price, according to a
regulatory filing today. That compares to a market value of 1.45
billion reais at the end of last week, data compiled by
Bloomberg show.  Rossi Residencial SA (RSID3)  (RSID3 BS) fell 6.1 percent to 13.32
reais.  Brazil ’s sixth-biggest homebuilder by revenue dropped as
traders increased bets for higher borrowing costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
